        "title": "Treat unresolved rebase conflicts as needs_human",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nTreat unresolved rebase conflicts after a repair attempt as a terminal `needs_human` outcome instead of requeueing another repair attempt.\n\nThis is deterministic repair-executor behavior: if conflicts remain after the model edit pass, the report records the conflict blocker and exits as `needs_human`.\n\n## Scope\n\nModel-agnostic ClawSweeper executor behavior only. No model backend, OpenAI-compatible, adapter, or provider-specific code. Prompt wording is intentionally left out because that is handled separately.\n\n## Validation evidence\n\n```text\ncorepack pnpm run build:repair\nnode --test test/repair/execute-fix-artifact-source.test.ts\n```\n\nResult:\n\n```text\nbuild:repair: passed\nexecute-fix-artifact-source.test.ts: 7/7 tests passed\n```\n\nThe new regression covers:\n\n```text\nunresolved rebase conflicts are terminal needs_human repair reports\n```\n",
